oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Bluebird 78's - tape 5
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: Tape 5 of recordings of Bluebird 78 discs, featuring Joe's Acadians (performers), The Four Aces (performers), Happy Fats and his Rayne-Bo Ramblers (performers), Jean Fuselier (performer), and the Hackberry Ramblers (performers), performing Creole tunes from the 1930's.
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:creator: Joe's Acadians; The Four Aces; Happy Fats and his Rayne-Bo Ramblers; Jean Fuselier; Hackberry Ramblers
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dcterms:tableOfContents: Test tones -- La Two Step A Chachin (Joe's Acadians) -- Vous Avez Quitte Avec Que Une Dotre (The Four Aces) -- Lake Charles Waltz (The Four Aces) -- Chan Se Tige (Happy Fats and his Rayne-Bo Ramblers) -- La Robe Barre (Jean Fuselier) -- Chere Te Te (Jean Fuselier) -- Les Pauls Paus Pas (Joe's Acadians) -- [Unidentified] talks to Joe -- La Valse An Oncle Knute (Joe's Acadians) -- La Valse Du Veux Temps (Hackberry Ramblers)
